      "writtenOn": "2019-02-27T15:15:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I left this around by accident; a previous version of the code created an isolate.Task for every TaskSpec (hundreds, vs the 6 isolates we actually use) and passed them all to \"isolate batcharchive\".  That command should do a good job recognizing that there are only a handful of isolate files and avoid uploading files multiple times, but de-duplicating beforehand saves some work.",
      "parentUuid": "d5c23120_8ccf8a5b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 80,
        "startChar": 5,
