    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1164ac96_4e9277e1",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/cacher/cacher.go",
        "patchSetId": 23
      },
      "lineNbr": 94,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-27T15:15:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s actually pretty tricky to implement.  As written, we\u0027d need to inspect the dimensions specified by the TaskSpec and derive the OsType from them.  Honestly, I don\u0027t even know what the set of valid OsTypes are, and I think the only way it gets used is if the isolate itself has some if-condition regarding the OS.  For now, I think we\u0027re better off either using a different isolate if we want different behavior for different OS.  If we do decide we want this, I think the better option is to add an explicit \"IsolateOsType\" property to the TaskSpec so that we don\u0027t have to risk getting it wrong here.",
      "parentUuid": "59560b41_fd088891",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 94,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 94,
        "endChar": 53
      },
